-- Hungary Stocks: OTP, FHB Bank, Est Media Are Active in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-04-11T15:38:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-11/hungary-stocks-otp-fhb-bank-est-media-move-in-budapest-trade.html
Hungary ’s benchmark BUX stock index
dropped 0.9 percent to 17,874.85 as of the close in Budapest.
The following were among the most active equities in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, fell to
the lowest close in almost three months after the news website
Origo reported that Hungary plans to introduce a financial
transaction tax from next year. The shares dropped 1.9 percent
to 3,600 forint, the weakest level since Jan. 18.  Foldhitel es Jelzalogbank Nyrt.  (FHB HB), a Hungarian
mortgage lender, dropped 1.5 percent to 544 forint, the lowest
on a closing basis in a month.  Est Media Vagyonkezelo Nyrt. (ESTMEDIA HB), a Hungarian
entertainment company, capped the biggest five-day slide in 10
years. The company fell to the lowest on record after reporting
at the end of last week that its fourth-quarter net loss
widened. The shares declined 10 percent to 90 forint, extending
the drop in the last five trading sessions to 46 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
